A Newcastle taxi driver, who was killed in an ambush shooting along the N11, near Modelkloof turn-off, on Thursday morning, 16 July, was identified as 51-year-old Vusumuzi Ngwenya. Police told the Ladysmith Herald, that the taxi was travelling towards Newcastle, when the driver was shot and killed.  “The driver tried to drive off and crashed into a pole,” said police. It is believed that a vehicle with unknown gunmen started shooting at the taxi. “A case of murder was opened at the Ladysmith police station for investigation,” said Colonel Thembeka Mbele. The motive of the killing is suspected to be linked to taxi violence.